      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Suppress internal agent failure traces before channel delivery",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Move internal agent/tool trace-line stripping into the shared assistant-visible text sanitizer so non-Discord delivery users get the same suppression for failed-tool payloads.\n- Preserve Discord's stricter send-boundary guard for plain internal channel labels such as `analysis:`, `commentary:`, `thinking:`, and `reasoning:`.\n- Strip trace-only error-context payloads before user-facing delivery while preserving explicit tool-progress payloads and non-text Discord payloads.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/shared/text/assistant-visible-text.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers.sanitizeuserfacingtext.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/reply-delivery.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/message-handler.process.test.ts`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/followup-runner.test.ts -t \"tool progress\"`\n- `git diff --check`\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Internal agent/tool failure trace lines such as `⚠️ 🛠️ \\`run ... (agent)\\` failed` are no longer delivered as user-visible Discord messages when they are the only final text, and the generic assistant-visible sanitizer now removes the same trace shape for other delivery users. Discord delivery also continues to suppress plain internal channel-label lines such as `analysis:` and `commentary:` while still sending media, channelData, and presentation payloads when their text scrubs empty.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw source checkout on current `origin/main` after rebasing and follow-up commit `63376624dd`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/shared/text/assistant-visible-text.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-helpers.sanitizeuserfacingtext.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/reply-delivery.test.ts extensions/discord/src/monitor/message-handler.process.test.ts`; `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/followup-runner.test.ts -t \"tool progress\"`; `git diff --check`.\n\nEvidence after fix: Shared sanitizer tests strip warning/tool trace lines and preserve fenced examples and ordinary `Analysis:` headings; Discord delivery tests drop pure internal warning payloads and restored `analysis:`/`commentary:` channel-label payloads while preserving media/rich payloads when text scrubs empty; process tests confirm warning finals are suppressed instead of sent.\n\nObserved result after fix: Focused sanitizer and Discord tests passed; the tool-progress regression test passed with 4 matching tests and 63 skipped by filter; whitespace diff check passed.\n\nWhat was not tested: Live Discord delivery was not exercised in this checkout. The remaining Real behavior proof gate still needs redacted live Discord/Mantis evidence or maintainer override before merge.\n",
